xis angemessen zu bestimmen? Die Beiträge in vorliegendem Band widmen sich diesem Problemkomplex unter besonderer Berücksichtigung der Bereiche Moral und Wissenschaft.  aPeople argue about which actions are morally right or wrong, good or evil, permitted or forbidden. Can such questions be decided by reference to an objective moral truth? How can such truth be recognized? What role can the natural sciences play? What is the meaning of variations and changes in our ideas of morality? How much tolerance should we bring to divergent moral opinions, and when is criticism justified?  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 23. Jul 2020) 0aEthics. 0aScience. 0aTruth. 4aRealism. 4aRealismus. 4aToleranz. 4aWerte. 4atolerance. 4avalues. 7aPHILOSOPHY / Ethics & Moral Philosophy.2bisacsh1 aHeilinger, Jan-Christoph, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aNida-Rümelin, Julian, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus eBook-Package 2016z978311070100508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2016z9783110485103oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Philosophy 2016z9783110485301oZDB-23-DPH0 cEPUBz97831103873910 cprintz978311037894840uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311037900640uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110379006423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9783110379006.jpg  a978-3-11-070100-5  DG Plus eBook-Package 2016b2016  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA5EBK  aZDB-23-DGGb2016  aZDB-23-DPHb2016